534
00:36:23,908 --> 00:36:24,969
There were some this summer.

535
00:36:25,009 --> 00:36:26,050
There are more there now.

536
00:36:26,070 --> 00:36:28,853
I don't know if they're employees or customers of Oasis.

537
00:36:29,393 --> 00:36:32,797
But it's a motor vehicle that drives up onto the sidewalk.

538
00:36:35,582 --> 00:36:39,945
Residents and the general public need safe sidewalks to walk on, healthier to breathe.

539
00:36:40,205 --> 00:36:46,329
Schoolchildren in school buses who terminate at that corner need a safe zone for stops and walking.

540
00:36:46,609 --> 00:36:52,953
And the MBTA serving all citizens need a safe place to disembark and get on the bus.

541
00:36:53,013 --> 00:36:58,797
They need to have it closed, as these ladies have often mentioned.

542
00:36:59,497 --> 00:37:04,160
Currently, it's safer to walk on Main Street sometimes than it is to walk on the Harvard Street sidewalks.

543
00:37:04,601 --> 00:37:10,485
given the flow of traffic on the sidewalks, including the motorcycles, customer vehicles, delivery trucks, and bicycles.

544
00:37:11,686 --> 00:37:18,510
Reasons point to unchecked growth in a densely populated area, part of which I'm guilty of.

545
00:37:18,570 --> 00:37:22,473
We had 100 people move into the Lincoln County condos during 2009 and 2010.

546
00:37:27,261 --> 00:37:34,248
Prior to that, in 2006, Oasis owners spent a million dollars to buy a block of stores.

547
00:37:34,868 --> 00:37:45,599
They increased their small business area with limited seating to three storefronts on half the block, operating from 6 a.m.

548
00:37:45,699 --> 00:37:48,922
to 11 a.m., whether they had a permit to do so or not.

549
00:37:50,619 --> 00:37:56,280
They are now able to accommodate 200 seated guests or more in their restaurant.

550
00:37:56,720 --> 00:38:06,803
So we basically doubled the number of seats in a restaurant, the number of vehicles in that particular square over a very short period of time, over a four or five year period.

551
00:38:07,323 --> 00:38:11,844
None of the abutters were informed of the two expansions that Oasis went through.

552
00:38:12,084 --> 00:38:14,705
This is one thing we should look at with our city ordinances.

553
00:38:15,265 --> 00:38:19,906
How did they expand so rapidly without any notice to us, the abutters,

554
00:38:20,393 --> 00:38:25,914
any input from the abutters, and now we're seeing the results of it and begging for support.

555
00:38:29,955 --> 00:38:36,016
Two expansions, just double the size right to what Bocelli said, and forgive me for repeating myself.

556
00:38:36,796 --> 00:38:47,098
All of these expansions occurred without City Hall prior to 2016, adjusting limits, lending advice, or building a commerce support system

557
00:38:47,595 --> 00:39:00,665
such as moving a loading zone or adding a loading zone to support Oasis fitting into an already established neighborhood that was also expanding at the same time.

558
00:39:01,686 --> 00:39:08,771
I believe that Ron Lopez purchased the Lincoln School and the Kennedy School in 2007, and our unit was completed in 2010.

559
00:39:08,871 --> 00:39:16,417
This is a side note, but Oasis tripled in size over the past

560
00:39:17,272 --> 00:39:34,519
three years without increasing the size of their waste management facilities until the neighbors intervened due to chronically overflowing dumpsters filled to the brim and doubling the size with their smelly trash.

561
00:39:34,919 --> 00:39:36,899
That promoted the growth of rats in the area.

562
00:39:37,300 --> 00:39:42,362
The people who live at 159 have had rats infiltrating their patio during the summer.

563
00:39:43,062 --> 00:39:45,983
That was brought into control, yet we're seeing them again from

564
00:39:46,610 --> 00:39:50,851
in front of their condo, all the way down to Berwick, on the street, alive and dead.

565
00:39:51,411 --> 00:39:54,012
So that's one of the issues that the city is addressing at this point.

566
00:39:56,032 --> 00:40:04,294
Neighbors of South Medford Square have long felt their concerns have gone unheard or dismissed, much like the first complaints by the residents of Flint, Michigan, who complained about the water.

567
00:40:04,954 --> 00:40:14,096
We are of the opinion that parking enforcement is but one measure that can greatly improve residents' quality of life and easing of stress on the businesses in South Medford Square.

568
00:40:15,272 --> 00:40:23,675
We've been advocating through all relevant avenues available to us for City Hall to enforce the town's laws or the city's laws.

569
00:40:24,135 --> 00:40:26,216
These are not laws we're asking for.

570
00:40:26,256 --> 00:40:27,356
These are laws that exist.

571
00:40:28,237 --> 00:40:34,259
If you look at a parking ticket or a parking violation, parking on sidewalks, parking on hash marks, they're all there.

572
00:40:34,859 --> 00:40:44,843
We just don't have the manpower in the public safety groups, whether it be the Republic Parking or

573
00:40:45,947 --> 00:40:48,749
police department to support our own laws.

574
00:40:50,049 --> 00:40:51,330
And I think that's going to change.

575
00:40:51,370 --> 00:40:53,891
I can hope that changes with Mayor Burke.

576
00:40:55,372 --> 00:41:04,157
We need to support the traffic division, specifically in the police department, to move the trailer trucks and haulers off Harvard Street.

577
00:41:04,497 --> 00:41:07,699
We have many roadblocks and naysayers that add to this.

578
00:41:07,919 --> 00:41:09,960
We're not just dealing with trucks on the sidewalk.

579
00:41:10,360 --> 00:41:12,261
We're dealing with them hauling back and forth.

580
00:41:12,561 --> 00:41:13,882
So it's a tremendous area.

581
00:41:17,594 --> 00:41:21,816
For a long time, we didn't have the commercial centers with shops and restaurants.

