1283
01:39:12,860 --> 01:39:17,904
Back, I think it was a year and a half ago, I offered a resolution to create a trucking team.

1284
01:39:18,725 --> 01:39:21,527
Many surrounding police departments have a trucking team.

1285
01:39:22,288 --> 01:39:25,470
And it wasn't just to put on additional police officers.

1286
01:39:25,971 --> 01:39:33,977
It was to address an issue of 18 wheelers traversing our roads, Mr. President, and at no fear of ever getting pulled over.

1287
01:39:34,968 --> 01:39:44,195
It really is, from what I've been told by members of the police department, it's a particular training to pull these 18 wheelers over.

1288
01:39:44,215 --> 01:39:46,898
You have to have the ability to be able to look at the log.

1289
01:39:47,218 --> 01:39:58,366
You've got to have the ability to be able to read markings on the side of the truck, the type of liquids they may be carrying, the type of goods they may be carrying, the weight of the truck, and so forth.

1290
01:39:58,927 --> 01:40:04,251
And you have to have ample training, and you have to have the equipment to pull these trucks over.

1291
01:40:04,977 --> 01:40:12,598
And many of our police officers that I've spoken to aren't willing to pull these trucks over because they're not trained and not equipped.

1292
01:40:13,338 --> 01:40:15,059
And that was the statement I got from them.

1293
01:40:15,459 --> 01:40:19,860
So I think after a while, these truckers know, hey, you know what?

1294
01:40:19,900 --> 01:40:21,660
Don't go through Cambridge-Somerville.

1295
01:40:21,680 --> 01:40:23,280
Go through Method.

1296
01:40:23,520 --> 01:40:24,400
They won't pull you over.

1297
01:40:25,541 --> 01:40:29,341
And I think it's posing a problem in our community.

1298
01:40:29,981 --> 01:40:33,982
And again, I would ask for enforcement, Mr. President,

1299
01:40:34,355 --> 01:40:36,656
of the heavy trucking on Spring Street.

1300
01:40:37,776 --> 01:40:40,656
We all know what happens after a period of time with heavy trucking.

1301
01:40:41,116 --> 01:40:43,537
It creates the waves in the road.

1302
01:40:44,357 --> 01:40:45,137
It really does.

1303
01:40:45,597 --> 01:40:48,778
And we saw that firsthand on Spring Street in particular.

1304
01:40:49,158 --> 01:40:57,000
I'm not sure if it was poor quality of tar that was put down or whatever it might have been, but it created a lot of ripples throughout the whole road.

1305
01:40:57,340 --> 01:40:58,620
And that was from the heavy trucking.

1306
01:40:58,980 --> 01:41:01,741
So I would ask increased enforcement on Spring Street

1307
01:41:02,145 --> 01:41:08,032
And I would also ask the chief of police to once again look at the creation of a truck team.

1308
01:41:09,274 --> 01:41:16,843
I was told when you issue a ticket to an 18-wheeler, it could be upwards of $1,200 for a ticket.

1309
01:41:17,604 --> 01:41:20,288
So the truck unit would pay for itself.

1310
01:41:20,876 --> 01:41:22,257
doing the basic enforcement.

1311
01:41:22,477 --> 01:41:27,661
And don't forget, we have major truck routes running through our community, through our neighborhoods.

1312
01:41:28,402 --> 01:41:38,069
We saw what happened at Centilli Circle in Everett back some 10 years ago, when an 18-wheeler went off and went into the side of elderly housing over there.

1313
01:41:38,850 --> 01:41:45,535
These are trucks speeding through our community and so forth, and it really poses a public safety concern.

1314
01:41:45,555 --> 01:41:49,018
So I would ask that the chief look at the truck unit, Mr. President.

1315
01:41:49,714 --> 01:41:56,560
And if I could just put in a plug while I'm speaking, we also don't have police patrol on the Mystic River.

1316
01:41:57,561 --> 01:42:01,064
And people might say, oh, the Mystic River, you can walk over the Mystic River.

1317
01:42:01,584 --> 01:42:02,565
No, that's not the case.

1318
01:42:03,045 --> 01:42:07,609
We have Meffitt High School, our young students, rowing on the Mystic River.

1319
01:42:08,109 --> 01:42:14,475
And we don't have, other than the fire department, which does have a way of getting onto the Mystic River.

1320
01:42:15,318 --> 01:42:17,580
We don't have any patrol of the Mystic River at all.

1321
01:42:17,940 --> 01:42:21,562
We would have to wait for state police to come through the locks in Boston.

1322
01:42:21,863 --> 01:42:24,424
God forbid there was an accident on the Mystic River.

1323
01:42:25,325 --> 01:42:26,506
We've had tournaments there.

1324
01:42:26,786 --> 01:42:33,671
Just recently, the Meffitt Bowl Club had a tournament, a national tournament, actually, on the Mystic River.

1325
01:42:34,231 --> 01:42:43,377
And I think, really, as a city, we fall short of the mark when it comes to protecting our riverway and also protecting against these 18-wheelers

1326
01:42:45,048 --> 01:42:50,489
that are coming through our community without any fear of ever getting a ticket, Mr. President.

1327
01:42:50,809 --> 01:42:55,450
So I would offer those two, as well as the enforcement on Spring Street for the heavy trucking.

1328
01:42:55,870 --> 01:42:57,950
So the motion of Councilor Marks as amended.

1329
01:42:57,990 --> 01:42:58,570
Councilor Caviello.

1330
01:42:58,850 --> 01:42:59,531
Thank you, Mr. President.

1331
01:42:59,611 --> 01:43:02,211
I commend Councilor Marks on bringing this forward.

1332
01:43:02,811 --> 01:43:07,232
In the meantime, if the chief could contact the state police truck team.

1333
01:43:07,992 --> 01:43:14,033
I see them occasionally on Mystic Avenue pulling trucks over, occasionally on the parkway, but they're not anywhere else.

1334
01:43:14,617 --> 01:43:17,738
And he's right, when these trucks get pulled over, it's a pretty hefty fine.

1335
01:43:18,338 --> 01:43:27,321
So if he could contact the state police or the DOT truck team to maybe increase its presence in the Method area, it would be greatly helped.

1336
01:43:27,381 --> 01:43:33,002
And on the other thing you brought up, we have a position of harbormaster in the city.

1337
01:43:34,383 --> 01:43:36,843
What does the harbormaster do?

1338
01:43:37,304 --> 01:43:41,025
Is that something that should be looked upon as that safety?

1339
01:43:41,065 --> 01:43:42,445
I mean, who is the harbormaster?

1340
01:43:43,483 --> 01:43:44,684
That's my other question.

1341
01:43:45,844 --> 01:43:46,484
It's Mr. Burns.

1342
01:43:46,504 --> 01:43:57,670
I understand Mr. Burns is maybe a little, he's an older gentleman, and I don't think we own a boat either for the harbormaster.

1343
01:43:58,510 --> 01:44:07,754
So maybe something, maybe having a harbormaster that's a little more up with the times might be something for the new administration to look at.

1344
01:44:08,235 --> 01:44:08,775
Admiral Knight.

1345
01:44:09,866 --> 01:44:21,873
Mr. President, I ask to amend the paper to request that the chief of police provide us with the number of complaints that they received in the past 12 months relative to heavy trucking on residential roadways, as well as the number of citations issued.

1346
01:44:21,913 --> 01:44:22,414
Mr. President.

1347
01:44:22,914 --> 01:44:26,256
On the motion of Councilor Marks as amended.

1348
01:44:26,316 --> 01:44:27,236
All those in favor.

1349
01:44:27,977 --> 01:44:28,897
All those opposed.

1350
01:44:30,038 --> 01:44:33,000
Records of the previous week's meeting were passed to Councilor Marks.

1351
01:44:33,453 --> 01:44:35,375
Mr. Councilor, how did you find those records?

1352
01:44:35,896 --> 01:44:37,377
I reviewed the records, Mr. President.

1353
01:44:37,417 --> 01:44:38,979
I find them to be in order and move approval.

1354
01:44:39,159 --> 01:44:42,403
On the motion for approval of the previous records by Councilor Marks.

1355
01:44:42,463 --> 01:44:43,163
All those in favor?

1356
01:44:43,564 --> 01:44:44,305
All those opposed?

1357
01:44:44,345 --> 01:44:44,885
Motion carries.

1358
01:44:45,546 --> 01:44:47,688
On the motion of Councilor Caviello for adjournment.

1359
01:44:47,728 --> 01:44:48,469
All those in favor?

1360
01:44:49,310 --> 01:44:49,871
All those opposed?

1361
01:44:49,991 --> 01:44:50,672
Meeting adjourned.

